{"type":"message","id":"9c7e76bc","parentId":"b9813a8a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:45:31.193Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse script is still running. Let me check the most recent pulse log file while it runs.","thinkingSignature":"419e064d4f8e41ef57dccb68ef5fb15d93c9203368273ae9177a3322b3685bbf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8ospd05kob3z_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 154320.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8ospd05kob3z_2","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"lucky-bloom-2","timeout":55000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":409,"output":119,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12773,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774381527955}}
{"type":"message","id":"5f66ef6c","parentId":"9c7e76bc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:45:34.693Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8ospd05kob3z_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 154320\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 1 is complete - I have a clear compression experiment result\r\n2. The key insight is that CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals that need to be combined\r\n3. The next step is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n4. The formula is: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nI need to design the experiment to test this hypothesis. This means I need to:\r\n1. Create a test script or document that runs this experiment\r\n2. Compare against the binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120)\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take in this pulse. I should:\r\n- Design the experiment specification\r\n- Or create a script to run it\r\n- Or update the synthesis document with the experiment plan\r\n\r\nGiven the \"one concrete action\" constraint, I should create a focused experiment design document or script.\r\n\r\nLooking at the previous experiment, they ran 200 pulses with 80/20 split. For the hybrid experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Compute the hybrid score for each token\r\n2. Compare against binary thresholds\r\n3. Measure precision/recall on known important tokens\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete experiment script that can be run to test this hypothesis.\r\n\r\nThe key question: Does score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n\r\nFor \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00):\r\n- score = 1.0 × min(1, 160/120) = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (still scores high!)\r\n\r\n\r\n- For \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96):\r\n- score = 0.96 × min(1, 136/120) = 0.96 × 1.0 = 0.96 (still scores high!)\r\n\r\nI realize the normalization is ineffective for high-frequency tokens. I need to develop a more nuanced scoring approach that truly differentiates token types. The goal is to create a metric that captures meaningful variations between different token frequencies while preventing constant-format tokens from dominating the scoring.\r\n\r\nA potential solution involves a logarithmic or inverse frequency scaling that penalizes overly consistent tokens. This would help distinguish between truly informative tokens and repetitive structural elements.\r\n\r\nI'll design an experiment script that systematically tests different scoring strategies, comparing their effectiveness in identifying meaningful tokens across the dataset.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI×Freq^0.5 formula may not properly penalize constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) because the freq normalization (min(1, x/120)) caps at 1.0 for all tokens with freq ≥ 120, failing to distinguish them from research trajectory tokens like \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a refined hybrid scoring experiment script that tests a logarithmic frequency penalty: score(T) = CFI(T) × log(1 + freq(T)) / log(161). This ensures tokens at freq=160 score 1.0×(log(161)/log(161))=1.0, while \"Phase 1\" at freq=136 scores 0.96×(log(137)/log(161))=0.94, but importantly the formula still differentiates across the full frequency range.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```old_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C - Refined)\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** PLANNED\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe pure frequency normalization `min(1, freq/120)` caps at 1.0 for all tokens with freq ≥ 120, failing to distinguish:\r\n- **Constant format tokens**: freq=160, CFI=1.00 (\"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\")\r\n- **Research trajectory tokens**: freq=136, CFI=0.96 (\"Phase 1\")\r\n\r\n## Refined Scoring Formula\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × [log(1 + freq(T)) / log(161)]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis uses logarithmic scaling to differentiate across the full frequency range while maintaining CFI as the primary signal.\r\n\r\n### Expected Behavior\r\n| Token | freq | CFI | score |\r\n|-------|------|-----|-------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 × (log(161)/log(161)) = 1.00 |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 × 1.00 = 1.00 |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96 × (log(137)/log(161)) = 0.94 |\r\n| \"research\" | 80 | 0.70 | 0.70 × (log(81)/log(161)) = 0.57 |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 40 | 0.60 | 0.60 × (log(41)/log(161)) = 0.36 |\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n1. **Dataset:** 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split (reuse pulses from Strategy B)\r\n2. **Baseline:** Binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\r\n3. **Test:** Logarithmic scoring with threshold at score ≥ 0.40\r\n4. **Ground truth:** Manually labeled \"important\" vs \"metapro\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:43:40\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774381534689}}
{"type":"message","id":"ea8a07d7","parentId":"5f66ef6c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:45:44.672Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8ospd05kob3z_2","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4412\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3047\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1\r\n[mutation proposed] research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1\r\n[master fddff24] pulse: 2026-03-24 154519\n 6 files changed, 330 insertions(+), 70 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 154519.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 154519.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 154320.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 154519 - The CFI experiment revealed that binary thresholds fail on constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1). The next step is clear: implement and run the hybrid scoring experiment using score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) to see if it separates \"metaprogramming artifacts\" from \"research trajectory\".\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"lucky-bloom-2","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4412\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3047\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1\r\n[mutation proposed] research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1\r\n[master fddff24] pulse: 2026-03-24 154519\n 6 files changed, 330 insertions(+), 70 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 154519.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 154519.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 154320.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 154519 - The CFI experiment revealed that binary thresholds fail on constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1). The next step is clear: implement and run the hybrid scoring experiment using score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) to se