{"type":"message","id":"d56ec109","parentId":"3f9f1be7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:45:58.087Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rvwgva8bmto8_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 154519\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- Just completed CFI Compression Experiment with key findings\r\n- Next pending action: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n- Key insight: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) formula needs testing\r\n\r\nThe observation is that I just ran a CFI experiment and discovered that constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) are the trap. The next step is clearly to implement and run the hybrid scoring experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: implement the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment by creating the test script that will run the comparison.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI experiment revealed that binary thresholds fail on constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1). The next step is clear: implement and run the hybrid scoring experiment using score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) to see if it separates \"metaprogramming artifacts\" from \"research trajectory\".\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1` to test the hybrid scoring formula against binary thresholds, using the same 200-pulse dataset from the previous experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI Hybrid Scoring Experiment\r\n# Strategy C: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# Test: Does this distinguish constant-format (freq≈160, CFI=1) from research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n# Date: 2026-03-24\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$PulseDir = \"pulses\",\r\n    [int]$SampleSize = 200\r\n)\r\n\r\n. ./pulse_env.ps1\r\n\r\n$start = Get-Date\r\n\r\n# Load existing token data from prior experiment\r\n$tokenDataPath = \"research/token_data.json\"\r\nif (-not (Test-Path $tokenDataPath)) {\r\n    Write-Host \"[ERROR] token_data.json not found. Run cfi_experiment.ps1 first.\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\n$data = Get-Content $tokenDataPath | ConvertFrom-Json\r\n$allTokens = $data.tokens\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== HYBRID CFI×Freq SCORING EXPERIMENT ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Tokens loaded: $($allTokens.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Calculate hybrid score for each token\r\n$scoredTokens = $allTokens | ForEach-Object {\r\n    $freq = $_.frequency\r\n    $cfi = $_.cfi\r\n    $hybridScore = $cfi * [Math]::Min(1, $freq / 120)\r\n    \r\n    [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        token = $_.token\r\n        freq = $freq\r\n        cfi = $cfi\r\n        hybridScore = [Math]::Round($hybridScore, 4)\r\n        isConstantFormat = ($freq -ge 120 -and $cfi -ge 0.95)\r\n        isResearchTrajectory = ($cfi -ge 0.5 -and $freq -ge 3 -and $freq -lt 120)\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Test hybrid scoring thresholds\r\n$thresholds = @(0.3, 0.4, 0.5, 0.6, 0.7)\r\n$results = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($thresh in $thresholds) {\r\n    $selected = $scoredTokens | Where-Object { $_.hybridScore -ge $thresh }\r\n    \r\n    $constantCount = ($selected | Where-Object { $_.isConstantFormat }).Count\r\n    $trajectoryCount = ($selected | Where-Object { $_.isResearchTrajectory }).Count\r\n    $totalCount = $selected.Count\r\n    \r\n    $precision = if ($totalCount -gt 0) { $trajectoryCount / $totalCount } else { 0 }\r\n    \r\n    $results += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        threshold = $thresh\r\n        selected = $totalCount\r\n        trajectory = $trajectoryCount\r\n        constant = $constantCount\r\n        precision = [Math]::Round($precision, 4)\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== HYBRID SCORING RESULTS ===\"\r\n$results | Format-Table -AutoSize\r\n\r\n# Find optimal threshold\r\n$optimal = $results | Sort-Object -Property precision -Descending | Select-Object -First 1\r\nWrite-Host \"OPTIMAL: threshold=$($optimal.threshold), precision=$($optimal.precision), selected=$($optimal.selected)\"\r\n\r\n# Compare with binary thresholds from prior experiment\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"=== COMPARISON WITH PRIOR BINARY RESULTS ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Binary CFI≥0.5 only: precision=0.5653 (92.9% recall loss)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Binary CFI≥0.7 only: precision=0.5653 (92.9% recall loss)\"  \r\nWrite-Host \"Binary freq<120:    precision=0.4254 (baseline)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Hybrid threshold=$($optimal.threshold): precision=$($optimal.precision)\"\r\n\r\n# Show examples of scoring\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"=== EXAMPLE SCORING ===\"\r\n$examples = @(\r\n    @{token=\"for next instantiation\"; freq=160; cfi=1.0},\r\n    @{token=\"pulse\"; freq=160; cfi=1.0},\r\n    @{token=\"Phase 1\"; freq=136; cfi=0.96},\r\n    @{token=\"architecture\"; freq=45; cfi=0.72}\r\n)\r\n\r\nforeach ($\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:45:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774381558084}}
{"type":"message","id":"809ea6cb","parentId":"d56ec109","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:46:07.128Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me summarize the pulse concisely.","thinkingSignature":"4531125d32cab2dc62596469b39a8d561327bb5d0bf0f325b1f29a0a53cea4d3"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 15:45**\n\n**✅ Completed:**\n- CFI Compression Experiment (Strategy B) finished — key finding: binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)) suffer 92.9% recall loss because constant-format tokens like `\"for next instantiation\"` and `\"pulse\"` (freq ≈ 160, CFI = 1.0) are indistinguishable from true research trajectory tokens like `\"Phase 1\"` (freq = 136, CFI = 0.96)\n\n**🔬 Next Action:**\n- Create `research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1` to test the hybrid formula: `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)`\n\n**📁 Mutations:**\n- 1 new proposed mutation waiting (the hybrid experiment script)\n- Previous mutation from 154320 was **rejected** (residual, the newer approach superseded it)\n\n**📊 Key Insight:**\nCFI and frequency are **orthogonal signals** — the hybrid scoring needs to combine them without the normalization capping out for high-frequency tokens. The experiment will determine if the hybrid formula can properly distinguish constant-format artifacts from real research trajectory."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3393,"output":274,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15912,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774381558108}}
